sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1087023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was constructed by assemblying BBa_K145215 and BBa_K1087022 to test the function of riboregulator and phiR73 activator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tong Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K145215
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
FILTER This device was designed to filter out noise in an input signal; in our case OmpF PoPs. If there is a short increase in transcription from this promoter, a small amount of J23066 RiboKey is produced. This is then used to unlock (J23078) the short lived UmuD-tagged T7 RNA polymerase. This results in an increase of active T7 protein.
The final part of this filter is an AND gate which is used in the components further on in the system. This AND gate consists of a T7 RNA polymerase promoter with another RiboLock (J23078 again). The AND gate will only function if the duration of the noise is sufficiently long and intense (= a signal) in order to have both the short-lived RiboKey AND T7 polymerase available at the same time and thus to produce the component.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We did a lot of modeling on this device. The most efficient Berkeley 2006 key and lock have been used. The RiboKy might be required in higher copy number although modeling doesn't predict this.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jonas Demeulemeester

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1087022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was constructed by assemblying BBa_K1087007 and BBa_K1087018 to test the function of ribolock and phiR73
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tong Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J23008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part has the same homology region to J01122 as J23007 except that unlike J23007, J23008 does not contain the hairpin that was derived from J01129. J23008 anneals linearly to the stem of the hairpin in J01122 with perfect base pairing and destroys the hairpin in the process and reveals the RBS on J01122. When J01122 is transcribed the RNA secondary structure is such that the RBS hairpins with sequence upstream preventing the ribosome from binding and translation from occuring thereby locking up RFP further down stream. When J23008 is introduced into the cell in trans, we suspect that it will unlock the RBS for RFP as described above allowing translation to occur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kaitlin Davis

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J23009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Variant of key3 (see part J01129 (key3), J23007(key3b), J23008(key3c)). Part is in pJ23006, so there is a Ptet upstream of the XbaI site to drive expression. Nevertheless, J23009 is still a basic part allowing both prefix and suffix insertions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1087007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In this part,the expression of PhiR73 activator is controlled by the riboregulator lock3d. When this part is cotransfected with the key BBa_K145215, the "lock" can be opened and the PhiR73 activator can be expressed to induce its promoters such as BBa_I746361.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tong Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1087018

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1087004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is riboregulator that can express downstream gene with a key BBa_K145215, while "lock" it without the key.We assemblied this part as an alternative to BBa_I714070 which has a poor quality and cannot be transformed from the kit plate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tong Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13507

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was PCRed from BBa_K1087005 to get rid of the RBS, so one can use this part with a riboregulator such as BBa_K1087004.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tong Xu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746361
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of the DNA is the P2 phage genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PO promoter taken from the P2 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PO promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
